div.p: The StepFunctions state machine consists of 10 states, each of which performs a specific task or decision.
The IngestData task state submits an EMR job to ingest data from a Kafka cluster and retries up to 6 times if errors occur.

p.span: pauses state machineto avoid polling the EMR job status frequently.
states monitor, and evaluate the job status.
Similar pattern of 4 tasks applies to the next step started with
Finally, NotifySuccess and NotifyFailure states send notifications based on the success or failure of the pipeline.

div.div: The CloudWatch Dashboard provides an overview of pre-initialized capacity vs. OnDemand as well as drill-down metrics for CPU, memory, and disk usage for Spark Drivers and Executors.Pre-initialized capacity is an optional feature of EMR Serverless that keeps driver and workers pre-initialized and ready to respond in seconds and this dashboard can help understand if pre-initialized capacity is being used effectively.
In addition, one can see job-level metrics for the state of your jobs on a per-application basis

div.p: Use AWS CLI and CloudFormaton to create stacks of S3 buckets, parameters in Systems Manager Parameter Store, task for EventBridge
Also deploys CloudWatch Dashboard for Spark applications on EMR Serverless.

Also not shown here, but required to support resources, are two Amazon Virtual Private Clouds (VPCs), at least three subnets, multiple AWS Identity and Access Management (IAM) Roles and Policies, Security Groups and Route Tables, and a VPC Gateway Endpoint for S3.
